---
title: Logistikos — Order creation sequence (async pipeline)
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor Customer
    participant Frontend as React Frontend
    participant Controller as Rails Controller
    participant Service as Orders::Creator
    participant Sidekiq as Sidekiq Queue
    participant Geocode as GeocodeWorker
    participant Route as RouteCalcWorker
    participant Price as PriceEstimationWorker
    participant Match as DriverMatchWorker
    participant DB as Supabase PostGIS

    Customer->>Frontend: Fill order form
    Frontend->>Controller: POST /delivery_orders (Inertia)
    Controller->>Service: Orders::Creator.call(params)
    Service->>DB: INSERT DeliveryOrder (status: processing)
    Service->>Sidekiq: Enqueue GeocodeWorker

    Service-->>Controller: order (status: processing)
    Controller-->>Frontend: Inertia redirect (order show)
    Frontend-->>Customer: "Order submitted! Processing..."

    Note over Sidekiq,DB: Async pipeline begins

    Sidekiq->>Geocode: Execute
    activate Geocode
    Geocode->>DB: PostGIS geocode(pickup_address)
    DB-->>Geocode: pickup lat/lng
    Geocode->>DB: PostGIS geocode(dropoff_address)
    DB-->>Geocode: dropoff lat/lng
    Geocode->>DB: UPDATE pickup_location, dropoff_location
    Geocode->>Sidekiq: Enqueue RouteCalcWorker
    deactivate Geocode

    Sidekiq->>Route: Execute
    activate Route
    Route->>DB: pgr_dijkstra(pickup → dropoff)
    DB-->>Route: route geometry + distance + duration
    Route->>DB: UPDATE route_geometry, distance, duration
    Route->>Sidekiq: Enqueue PriceEstimationWorker
    Route->>Sidekiq: Enqueue DriverMatchWorker
    deactivate Route

    Sidekiq->>Price: Execute
    activate Price
    Price->>DB: Calculate price (distance, load, time)
    Price->>DB: UPDATE estimated_price
    deactivate Price

    Sidekiq->>Match: Execute
    activate Match
    Match->>DB: ST_DWithin(driver_location, pickup, radius)
    DB-->>Match: eligible drivers[]
    Match->>DB: INSERT notifications (batch)
    Match->>DB: UPDATE order status → open
    deactivate Match

    Note over Customer,DB: Order now visible in driver feed
